// Golden fixture for the deterministic replay contract (T-1003).
//
// The replay test asserts a fresh replay of these logs reproduces the COMMITTED
// golden strings below — not a second live replay of the same function (which
// would be tautological). A drift here is a real determinism regression (or a
// deliberate rebalance): regenerate with
//
//     npx tsx packages/sim/src/__tests__/fixtures/gen-golden.ts
//
// which imports these logs, runs replay(), and prints the exact constants to
// paste back. Two logs are committed because no single seed naturally surfaces
// every PlayerAction type in one day-loop:
//   - REPLAY_LOG:        Trade (buy-fuel/sign-contract/haggle/pay-debt), Travel,
//                        Explore, Shipyard (all four kinds: repair,
//                        buy-cargo-pods, buy-component-tier,
//                        buy-special-equipment), VisitHangout (T-1303), Storylet,
//                        Wait.
//   - REPLAY_LOG_COMBAT: sign-contract + Travel into a seeded encounter, then
//                        Combat in all three stances — fight (hull 2 -> 1),
//                        run (failed OPPOSED pilot roll, T-1207), talk (failed
//                        check) — the unresolved encounter carries across
//                        end-day, and a day-2 fight lands the killing volley but
//                        the interceptor pulls a natural-20 retreat (T-1207
//                        "miracle burn") → resolution `interceptor-escaped`, the
//                        pending travel still completing (the player won the
//                        field). This seed's day-2 retreat d20 comes up 20, so
//                        the replay exercises the miracle-burn path end to end.
//                        Seed 1's first jump to system 2 deterministically
//                        triggers the encounter with interceptor `npc-the-chef`.
// Between them, every PlayerAction discriminant is exercised — and at
// sub-action granularity every Trade sub-action, every ShipyardActionKind, and
// every Combat stance (asserted by the coverage guard in protocol.test.ts).
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

import type { ProtocolRequest } from '../../protocol.js';

/** Primary coverage log (seed 5): two day-loops covering every non-combat
 *  PlayerAction type. */
